genresAdvancedInfo.name: chamorro pop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Chamorro pop is a genre of music that originated in the Mariana Islands and is heavily influenced by American pop music. It features catchy melodies, upbeat rhythms, and lyrics sung in the Chamorro language. The genre has evolved over time to incorporate elements of reggae, hip-hop, and other popular styles.
